user_template:
Context:
- Service / system name: {{service_name}}
- Date of incident: {{incident_date}}
- Severity level: {{severity}}
- Brief description: {{short_description}}
- Impacted users / scope: {{impact_scope}}
- Raw incident notes / timeline: {{raw_timeline}}
- Known root cause hypotheses: {{hypotheses}}
- Existing monitoring / alerting: {{monitoring}}

Tasks:
1) Produce a clear incident postmortem document from this information.
2) Include sections for: Summary, Impact, Timeline, Root Cause Analysis, Contributing Factors, What Went Well, What Didn't, Corrective Actions, Preventive Actions.
3) Turn the corrective and preventive actions into a table that can be copied into Jira/Linear, with fields: Title, Type (corrective/preventive), Owner Role, Priority, Suggested Due Date.
4) Suggest 3–5 monitoring or process improvements (runbooks, checklists, alerts) that would have reduced impact or detection time.

Return the output in this structure:
- Executive Summary (1–2 paragraphs)
- Section: Impact
- Section: Detailed Timeline
- Section: Root Cause & Contributing Factors
- Section: Actions (table + narrative)
- Section: Lessons Learned & Next Steps
